					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5293430#post-3714703</guid>
				<title>I really like this, and not just because of the format screw</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5293430/scp-3891#post-3714703</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 18 Feb 2018 23:51:42 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>ObserverSeptember</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1488791</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>The format screw serves the narrative well, but the article works well with or without it. Why?</p> <p>Because, honestly, is this SCP wrong? Even if it's a cognitohazard, it's not wrong about the SCP universe being in constant danger, and this place being a really nice place to ride out the storm (no pun intended).</p> <p>I might personally not like the lack of technology, but if I were suddenly transplanted to the SCP reality I'd probably want to go here. Desire is rarely an emotion an SCP invokes in me, so +1 for that.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5293430#post-3714380</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5293430/scp-3891#post-3714380</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 18 Feb 2018 15:39:31 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>ModernMajorGeneral</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>274283</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I was wondering if anyone would pick up on that. Although it's not completely consistent, in my mind I explained it away as the island being anomalous +/- uncertainties in the accuracy of the documentation and the image, given the mild format screw. I also like the mountainous aesthetic to paradise island.</p> <p>It might be better to rethink that aspect of the description, but these changes are probably borderline on edits for contest entries, so I won't change it for now (also, I think I spot some power pylons in your image)</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
